      "raw_text": "special Correspondence to The Press\nOF the house. She is in Washing\nton working in behalf of woman\nsuffrage, with indifference success.\nMembers who in the old days would\nhave given eager ear, fearful of the\ndispleasure of the czar, now fatty\nrefuse to admit that their sisters\nshould have any voice in govern\ning the country.\n\n\nMrs. Ballentine has all but aban-\ndoned her chosen profession. When\nshe graduated at the head of her\nclass from womans law school, a\nbrilliant career was prophesied for\nher. Marriage destroyed the idea\nof practicing at the bar, although\nshe is an applicant for one of the\nlegal positions under the war de-\npartment."
